titleStmt.title: Thursday, January 5. 1659. Resolved, that upon the whole matter of the report touching absent members, ...
titleStmt.author: England and Wales. Parliament.

publicationStmt.publisher: Printed by John Streater, and John Macock, Printers to the Parliament,

notesStmt.note: Title from caption and first line of text.

A resolution of Parliament, "that the Members who stand discharged from voting or sitting as Members of this House in the years 1648, 1649, do stand duely discharged from sitting as Members of this Parliament."
Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
